==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pintle
<hw>Pin"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A diminutive of
<er>Pin</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A little pin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>An upright pivot pin</def>; as:
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The pivot pin of a hinge.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A
hook or pin on which a rudder hangs and turns.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A
pivot about which the chassis swings, in some kinds of gun
carriages.</def> <sd>(d)</sd> <def>A kingbolt of a wagon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinto</ent>⟦br⟧
